cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of reconstructing 3D facial geometry from a single 2D image using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a CNN on a dataset, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with volumetric representation of 3D facial geometry, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also involves facial landmark localization, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves direct regression of 3D facial geometry, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
